{"bill":{"bill_id":1652740,"change_hash":"09a4c1d5925e2d07c6758a0d10e6c966","session_id":1988,"session":{"session_id":1988,"state_id":46,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/VA\/bill\/HB2137\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/lis.virginia.gov\/cgi-bin\/legp604.exe?231+sum+HB2137","completed":0,"status":3,"status_date":"2023-02-23","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-10","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-10","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-03","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-06","event":2},{"date":"2023-02-08","event":9},{"date":"2023-02-16","event":10},{"date":"2023-02-23","event":3}],"state":"VA","state_id":46,"bill_number":"HB2137","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"H","body_id":7,"current_body":"S","current_body_id":8,"title":"School boards; divisionwide literacy plans.","description":"School boards; divisionwide literacy plans; contents; posting. Requires each divisionwide literacy plan to be submitted to the Department of Education and to identify which core literacy curricula, supplemental instructional practices and programs, and intervention programs from the list developed by the Department or alternative programs approved by the Department that consist of evidence-based literacy instruction and align with science-based reading research will be used in each grade level, kindergarten through 12, at each of the schools within such school division. The bill requires each local school board to post, maintain, and update as necessary on such school board's website a copy of its divisionwide literacy plan and the job description and contact information for any reading specialist employed by such school division pursuant to relevant law and for any dyslexia specialist employed by such school division. The bill requires the Department to post each divisionwide literacy plan on its website. School boards; divisionwide literacy plans; contents; posting. Requires each divisionwide literacy plan to be submitted to the Department of Education and to identify which core literacy curricula, supplemental instructional practices and programs, and intervention programs from the list developed by the Department or alternative programs approved by the Department that consist of evidence-based literacy instruction and align with science-based reading research will be used in each grade level, kindergarten through 12, at each of the schools within such school division. The bill requires each local school board to post, maintain, and update as necessary on such school board's website a copy of its divisionwide literacy plan and the job description and contact information for any reading specialist employed by such school division pursuant to relevant law and for any dyslexia specialist employed by such school division. The bill requires the Department to post each divisionwide literacy plan on its website.","pending_committee_id":0,"committee":[],"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-10","committee_id":151,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Education"},{"date":"2023-01-24","committee_id":4572,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Education: Early Childhood\/Innovation"},{"date":"2023-02-08","committee_id":163,"chamber":"S","chamber_id":8,"name":"Education and Health"}],"history":[{"date":"2023-01-10","action":"Prefiled and ordered printed; offered 01\/11\/23 23103666D","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-10","action":"Referred to Committee on Education","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-24","action":"Assigned Education sub: Early Childhood\/Innovation","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-25","action":"Subcommittee recommends reporting (7-Y 0-N)","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-03","action":"Reported from Education with substitute (22-Y 0-N)","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"im